             = \n| coordinates_type                = \n| coordinates_region              = \n| subdivision_type1               = [[States and territories of India|State]]\n| subdivision_name1               = [[Telangana]]\n| seat_type                       = [[Core city]]\n| seat                            = [[Hyderabad]]\n| parts_type                      = [[List of districts of India|Districts]]\n| parts                           = {{ubl|\n[[Hyderabad District, India|Hyderabad District]]|[[Medchal district]]|[[Rangareddy district]]|[[Siddipet district]]|[[Yadadri Bhuvanagiri district]]|[[Sangareddy district]]}}\n| population_total                = {{Estimation}} 9,580,000<ref name=pop> http://www.demographia.com/db-worldua.pdf </ref>\n| population_as_of                = 2019\n| population_footnotes            = \n| area_total_km2                  = 7257\n| area_footnotes                  = <ref name=\"hmda\">{{cite web|url=http://www.hmda.gov.in/About.aspx |title=About HMDA |publisher=Hyderabad Metropolitan Development Authority |access-date=2018-10-07}}</ref>\n| population_density_km2          = 10,477\n| population_demonym              = Hyderabadi\n| timezone1                       = [[Indian Standard Time]]\n| utc_offset1                     = +5:30\n| website                         = {{URL|http://www.hmda.gov.in/}}\n \n}}\n\n'''Hyderabad Metropolitan Region''' is the metropolitan area covered by the city of [[Hyderabad]] in the Indian state of [[Telangana]]. The entire region is spread over the districts of [[Hyderabad District, India|Hyderabad District]], [[Medchal district|Medchal]], [[Ranga Reddy district|Ranga Reddy]], [[Sangareddy district|Sangareddy]], [[Medak district|Medak]], [[Siddipet district|Siddipet]] and [[Yadadri Bhuvanagiri district|Yadadri Bhuvanagiri]]. Under the jurisdiction of [[Hyderabad Metropolitan Development Authority]], it covers an area of {{convert|7257|sqkm|abbr=on}} and has a population of 9.58 million people.<ref name=pop/>\n[